Module kivakit.interfaces
Package com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection

Interface Addable<Value>

All Superinterfaces:
Emptiness, Sized, SpaceLimited
All Known Subinterfaces:
Sectionable<Value,Section>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseCollection, BaseIndexedMap, BaseList, BaseResourceList, BaseSet, Batcher.BatchAdder, ConcurrentHashSet, FileList, FolderList, IdentitySet, IndexedNameMap, LinkedObjectList, MessageList, ObjectList, ObjectSet, ResourceList, Stack, StringList, ValidationIssues
public interface Addable<Value> extends SpaceLimited
An object, often a collection or related type, to which objects can be added. Provides default implementations for adding values from objects that implement Iterable or Iterator. Note that all Java collections are Iterable, so they can be added with addAll(Iterable)
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
